        "smallTitle9D": "HMI screen view",
        "text9D": "Alarms that have disappeared are shown in white. The alarms are acknowledged by pressing the button (level 1 required).The date and time when the alarm was triggered are indicated on the left. The number of times the alarm has been triggered is shown on the right. The alarm counter is reset by selecting the alarm table and pressing the button (level 1 required).The deletion of a disappeared alarm is done by selecting the line concerned and then pressing the \"Delete\" button (level 1 required). To delete all the missing alarms, select the alarm table and press the \"Delete all\" button (level 1 required).",
        "FB001": {
            "title1": "Description for function bloc [@]",
            "subTitle1": "General description",
            "text1": "This is a completely custom installation, however some elements are same, for them we will use the function block programming method (FB).The instrumentation will be managed by standardized blocks, in order to ensure homogenization of the programming. These blocks are used only in the process PLC, this chapter presents their functionalities.",
