        "title18": "Alarms management",
        "subTitle18": "Introduction",
        "text18": "Security management share four “big” family of faults.All faults family when triggered set a synthesis and fault message on HMI alarms screen.An acknowledgment request can acquit and reset default. Alarms are classified into 2 categories:",
        "smallTitle18A": "Minor",
        "text18A": "Warning without immediate impact on the system's capacity to ensure the main functions of the process or when the state of a measurement approaches the ultimate limits of a process. Without treatment, a minor alarm can lead to a major alarm due to the evolution of the phenomenon. This type of alarm can be treated within a few days and allows to avoid major alarms.",
        "smallTitle18B": "Major",
        "text18B": "State of an equipment making it inoperable or a state of a measure having exceeded the ultimate specifications of a process.This type of alarm must be treated as an emergency to avoid loss of production and/or risk of damage to equipment.",
